        <div class="story">
          <h5>Her Story</h5>
          <p>
            How we met was a story of a first impression soiled by a bad mood, a trip to Ken's Donuts enhanced by a bottle of whole milk, and a random walk down Martin Luther King Jr. Blvd. Our friendship grew over two continents, through sad book recommendations and sporadic, poorly-connected conversations, as I lived out, vicariously, a journey through Europe over the 0's and 1's of Facebook messenger.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our 5000-mile friendship would prove to be good practice for what would become 3.5 years of a long distance relationship. In the summer of 2013, when Joshua and I began dating, he was off to Fort Worth to begin his first year of adulthood, and I was a rising junior in college, struggling to figure out my place in society (so dramatic, I know, but so true). Our story, spanning two years and two continents, and then two cities, would then grow to span two states in 2015, when Joshua moved to California for graduate school.
          </p>
          <p>
            People that know us well know that Joshua and I are polar opposites in many ways, and these differences manifested in the highs and, especially, the lows of our relationship throughout the 5.5 years we've been together. Over the years, we've both grown so much in understanding and love for each other, with the help of (remarkable) patience on both ends and, significantly, love, support, and prayers of our best friends.
          </p>
          <p>
            I could say more, but just watch how Joshua made me say yes*, and you'll see (just a glimpse of) the laughter, the tears, the music, the pups, the friends, and, most importantly, the ever-growing love that brought us to where we are today...and will bring us to and through our next chapter of life together!!! It's crazy to think that the boy I danced to Gangnam Style with outside of Chick-Fil-A at age 19 is now the man I am marrying in just a couple of months!!!
          </p>
          <p class="footnote">
            *shouts out to and shameless plug for the amazing <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.gentlycraftedfilms.com/">Gently Crafted Films</a>! For more of my story - both "how we met" and "the proposal" - and a plethora of super cute pictures taken by Amanda and Ezra Gentle, check out <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://howheasked.com/ingrid-and-joshua/">this link</a>!
          </p>
          <p>
            
          </p>
